{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pie Crust","content":["Line a pie pan with one pie crust dough. Roll out the second pie dough to ¼ inch thick. Cut rolled dough into strips (½ in.-1 in.). Refrigerate pie crust and dough strips for 15 minutes. Meanwhile prepare apples."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Core, peel and slice apples (¼ in.). Place a large bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in 32 oz apple slices. Add lemon juice, toss to coat and set aside.","Place crème fraîche, 1 egg, sugar, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, ginger, salt and vanilla into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Place reserved sliced apples into chilled pie dough, piled high in the middle. Pour crème fraîche mixture evenly over apples. Create a lattice crust on top of apples with prepared dough strips and chill in freezer for 15 minutes.","Preheat oven to 425°F. Place 1 egg into a bowl and lightly whisk with a fork.","Brush top of pie with whisked egg, sprinkle with turbinado sugar and bake for 25 minutes (425°F). Reduce oven temperature to 375°F and bake 30-40 minutes (375°F), until golden brown. Let cool completely before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pie Crust","content":["2 homemade pie crusts, chilled (9 in.)"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["6 Pink Lady apples (approx. 44 oz)","1 tbsp lemon juice","6 oz crème fraîche","2 large eggs, divided","2 oz sugar","1 oz brown sugar","1 oz all-purpose flour","1 tsp ground cinnamon","½ tsp ground ginger","¼ tsp salt","1 ½ tsp vanilla extract","1 tbsp turbinado sugar              (optional)"]}],"id":"r254142","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-dWNnlYS8lE0\/XZWcheqmpPI\/AAAAAAAAea0\/gugbqc49xuQ--hwMYixMDh2odp8OSlmSQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_0WRrO9LPlMpoVF-U.png","title":"Crème Fraîche Apple Pie","publishedAt":"2017-11-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"20 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"61 g","calories":"1807 kJ \/ 432 kcal"},"usefulItems":"pie pan (approx. 9 in.), pastry brush, large bowl, ref